entry.summary:
Abstract Within the framework of p-adaptive flux reconstruction, we aim to construct efficient polynomial multigrid (pMG) preconditioners for implicit time integration of the Navier–Stokes equations using Jacobian-free Newton–Krylov (JFNK) methods. We hypothesise that in pseudo transient continuation (PTC), as the residual drops, the frequency of error modes that dictates the convergence rate gets higher and higher. We apply nonlinear pMG solvers to stiff steady problems at low Mach number (
\(\textrm{Ma}=10^{-3}\)
) to verify our hypothesis. It is demonstrated that once the residual drops by a few orders of magnitude, improved smoothing on intermediate p-sublevels will not only maintain the stability o…
